(22, 'Configuring FreePBX with Twilio for Bitrix Integration', 'configure-freepbx', NULL, NULL, '<div class=\"content pb-0\">\r\n  <div class=\"for-two-column content-holder\">\r\n    <h2 id=\"overview\">Overview</h2>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n      This documentation provides a basic configuration to get FreePBX up and\r\n      running with Twilio SIP Trunking for Bitrix Integration.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n      To get started with FreePBX for Bitrix Integration you would need to do\r\n      the following:\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <ol class=\"numbered\">\r\n      <li>\r\n        <a href=\"#installation-of-freepbx\">Installing FreePBX using AWS AMI</a>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        <a href=\"#installation-of-letsencrypt\"\r\n          >Installing SSL using LetsEncrypt</a\r\n        >.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li><a href=\"#configuring-sip-settings\">Configuring Sip Settings</a>.</li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        <a href=\"#create-a-trunk\"\r\n          >Create a Trunk on FreePBX with Twilio Elastic SIP Trunking</a\r\n        >.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        <a href=\"#configuring-an-bitrix-module\"\r\n          >Configure the Bitrix Integration Module</a\r\n        >.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        <a href=\"#configuring-an-outbound-trunk\">Configure an Outbound Trunk</a\r\n        >.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        <a href=\"#configuring-an-inbound-trunk\">Configure the Inbound Trunk</a>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li><a href=\"#configuring-zoiper\">Configure Zoiper SoftPhone</a>.</li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n\r\n    <h2 id=\"create-a-trunk-on-zentrunk\">Create a Trunk on Zentrunk</h2>\r\n\r\n    <p>\r\n      You can create a trunk using Plivo Console. For more information on\r\n      creating a Trunk on Plivo Console, see\r\n      <a\r\n        href=\"https://www.plivo.com/docs/sip-trunking/getting-started-with-zentrunk/\"\r\n        >Getting Started with Zentrunk</a\r\n      >.\r\n    </p>\r\n\r\n    <h2 id=\"configuring-an-outbound-trunk\">Configuring an Outbound Trunk</h2>\r\n\r\n    <p>Configuring your Outbound Trunk involves the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n    <ol class=\"numbered\">\r\n      <li>Adding a Trunk</li>\r\n      <li>Adding Outbound Routes</li>\r\n      <li>Configuring an Extension</li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Configuring X-Lite <strong>Note:</strong> There are many softphones that\r\n        you can use (for example, X-Lite, Blink for Linux, etc). In this\r\n        tutorial, we will be using the X-Lite Softphone.\r\n      </li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n\r\n    <h3 id=\"to-add-a-trunk\">To add a trunk</h3>\r\n\r\n    <ol class=\"numbered\">\r\n      <li>\r\n        From your FreePBX dashboard, hover over the\r\n        <strong>Connectivity</strong> menu, and then click on\r\n        <strong>Trunks</strong>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        On the Trunks page, click <strong>Add Trunk</strong>, and then click\r\n        <strong>Add SIP (chan_sip) Trunk</strong>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        On the Add Trunk page, enter the following details in the General tab:\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>\r\n            <strong>Trunk Name</strong>: A friendly name for the trunk (for\r\n            example, demo-trunk)\r\n          </li>\r\n          <li>\r\n            <strong>Outbound Caller ID</strong>: Caller ID for the calls placed\r\n            using this trunk. This has to be in the following SIP format:\r\n            <div class=\"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge\">\r\n              <div class=\"highlight\">\r\n                <button\r\n                  class=\"highlight-copy__btn icon-copy\"\r\n                  title=\"Copy\"\r\n                ></button>\r\n                <pre class=\"highlight\">\r\n<code> &quot;demo&quot; <phone-number>\r\n</phone-number></code></pre>\r\n              </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n\r\n            <p>\r\n              <img\r\n                alt=\"Add Trunk Details\"\r\n                src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_0.png\"\r\n              />\r\n            </p>\r\n          </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Next, enter the following details in the\r\n        <strong>sip Settings</strong> tab:\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>\r\n            <strong>Host -</strong> Termination SIP Domain of your Plivo Trunk\r\n          </li>\r\n          <li><strong>Username -</strong> Username for TestAuthGroup</li>\r\n          <li><strong>Password -</strong> Password for TestAuthGroup</li>\r\n          <li>\r\n            <strong>Peer -</strong> Creates a peer connection\r\n            <img\r\n              alt=\"SIP Settings\"\r\n              src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_1.png\"\r\n            />\r\n          </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Add dial pattern, you can choose to match any specific digits or use\r\n        &ldquo;.&rdquo; as a wildcard to match one or more characters.\r\n        <img\r\n          alt=\"Dial Pattern\"\r\n          src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_2.png\"\r\n        />\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Enter a friendly name for the Trunk in the Trunk Name field, and then\r\n        click <strong>Submit</strong>. A trunk will be created. You must now\r\n        configure an outbound route to this trunk.\r\n      </li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n\r\n    <h3 id=\"to-add-an-outbound-route\">To add an outbound route</h3>\r\n\r\n    <ol class=\"numbered\">\r\n      <li>\r\n        From the <strong>Connectivity</strong> menu, click\r\n        <strong>Outbound Routes</strong>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        On the Outbound Routes page, click <strong>Add Outbound Route</strong>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        In the Outbound Route - Add Route page, enter a friendly name for the\r\n        route in the <strong>Route Name</strong> field.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        From the list of <strong>Trunk Sequence for Matched Routes</strong>,\r\n        select the trunk you created in the previous section (demo-outbound).\r\n        <img\r\n          alt=\"Select the Trunk\"\r\n          src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_3.png\"\r\n        />\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Next, on the Dial Patterns tab, enter the dial pattern that matches your\r\n        system. <strong>Note:</strong> You can choose to match any specific\r\n        digits or use &ldquo;.&rdquo; as a wildcard to match one or more\r\n        characters.\r\n        <img\r\n          alt=\"Select Dial pattern\"\r\n          src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_4.png\"\r\n        />\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Once you have entered your dial pattern, click <strong>Submit</strong>.\r\n        The outbound route will be configured to your trunk. You must now\r\n        configure an extension.\r\n      </li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n\r\n    <h3 id=\"to-add-an-extension\">To add an extension</h3>\r\n\r\n    <ol class=\"numbered\">\r\n      <li>\r\n        From the <strong>Applications</strong> menu, click\r\n        <strong>Extensions</strong>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        On the Extensions page, click\r\n        <strong>Add New Chan_SIP Extension</strong> from the\r\n        <strong>Add Extension</strong> list. The Add SIP Extension page appears.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        In the General tab, enter the following details:\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>\r\n            User Extension - The extension number to dial to reach the user\r\n          </li>\r\n          <li>\r\n            Display name - The callerID name for calls from this user will be\r\n            set to this name\r\n          </li>\r\n          <li>\r\n            Secret - Password configured for the device\r\n            <img\r\n              alt=\"Extension Details\"\r\n              src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_5.png\"\r\n            />\r\n          </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Once done, click <strong>Submit</strong>. Your extension is created.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        On the All Extensions tab, in the Actions column, click edit for your\r\n        extension.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        In the <strong>Advanced</strong> tab, under the\r\n        <strong>Edit Extension</strong> section, change the configuration for\r\n        <strong>NAT Mode</strong> to\r\n        <strong>Yes - (force_rport,comedia)</strong>.\r\n        <img\r\n          alt=\"Modify Extension\"\r\n          src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_6.png\"\r\n        />\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>Click <strong>Submit</strong>. Your extension will be created.</li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Asterisk SIP Settings</strong></p>\r\n\r\n    <ol class=\"numbered\">\r\n      <li>\r\n        From <strong>Setting</strong> menu, click\r\n        <strong>Asterisk SIP Settings</strong>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Next, enter the following details in the <strong>General</strong>\r\n        <strong>SIP Settings</strong> tab:\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>\r\n            <strong>External Address</strong> - Click on &lsquo;<strong\r\n              >Detect Network Settings</strong\r\n            >&rsquo; and copy the value for future reference\r\n            <img\r\n              alt=\"Asterisk SIP settings\"\r\n              src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_7.png\"\r\n            />\r\n          </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Next, enter the following details in the <strong>Chan</strong>\r\n        <strong>SIP Settings</strong> tab in\r\n        <strong>Advance General Settings</strong> section :\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li><strong>Bind port</strong> - 5060</li>\r\n          <li>\r\n            <strong>TLS Bind Port</strong> - 5061\r\n            <img\r\n              alt=\"Port Details\"\r\n              src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_8.png\"\r\n            />\r\n          </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Click <strong>Apply Config</strong> on the top navigation bar. All your\r\n        configurations are complete. You can now configure X-Lite to use your\r\n        Trunk. <strong>Note:</strong> In case you get an error while configuring\r\n        your softphone, make sure you have clicked\r\n        <strong>Apply Config</strong> on FreePBX.\r\n      </li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n\r\n    <h2 id=\"configuring-an-inbound-trunk\">Configuring an Inbound Trunk</h2>\r\n\r\n    <p>Configuring your Inbound Trunk involves the following steps:</p>\r\n\r\n    <ol class=\"numbered\">\r\n      <li>Configuring an Extension</li>\r\n      <li>Adding Inbound Routes</li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Configuring X-Lite <strong>Note:</strong> There are many softphones that\r\n        you can use (for example, X-Lite, Blink for Linux, etc). In this\r\n        tutorial, we will be using the X-Lite Softphone.\r\n      </li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n\r\n    <h3 id=\"to-add-an-extension-1\">To add an extension</h3>\r\n\r\n    <ol class=\"numbered\">\r\n      <li>\r\n        From the <strong>Applications</strong> menu, click\r\n        <strong>Extensions</strong>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        On the Extensions page, click\r\n        <strong>Add New Chan_SIP Extension</strong> from the\r\n        <strong>Add Extension</strong> list. The Add SIP Extension page appears.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        In the General tab, enter the following details:\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>\r\n            User Extension - The extension number to dial to reach the user\r\n          </li>\r\n          <li>\r\n            Display name - The callerID name for calls from this user will be\r\n            set to this name\r\n          </li>\r\n          <li>\r\n            Secret - Password configured for the device\r\n            <img\r\n              alt=\"Extension Details\"\r\n              src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_5.png\"\r\n            />\r\n          </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Once done, click <strong>Submit</strong>. Your extension is created.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        On the All Extensions tab, in the Actions column, click edit for your\r\n        extension.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        In the <strong>Advanced</strong> tab, under the\r\n        <strong>Edit Extension</strong> section, change the configuration for\r\n        <strong>NAT Mode</strong> to\r\n        <strong>Yes - (force_rport,comedia)</strong>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Addionally,check if rest of the values are configured in the below\r\n        format:\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>DTMF Signaling - RFC 2833</li>\r\n          <li>Connection Type - friend</li>\r\n          <li>\r\n            Port - 5060\r\n            <img\r\n              alt=\"Other Details\"\r\n              src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_6.png\"\r\n            />\r\n          </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>Click <strong>Submit</strong>. Your extension will be created.</li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n\r\n    <h3 id=\"to-add-an-inbound-route\">To add an inbound route</h3>\r\n\r\n    <ol class=\"numbered\">\r\n      <li>\r\n        From the <strong>Connectivity</strong> menu, click\r\n        <strong>Inbound Routes</strong>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        On the Inbound Routes page, click <strong>Add Inbound Route</strong>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        In the General tab, enter the following details:\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>\r\n            Description - Provide a meaningful description of what this incoming\r\n            route is\r\n          </li>\r\n          <li>\r\n            DID Number - Define the expected DID Number if your trunk passes DID\r\n            on incoming calls or leave it blank to match calls with any or no\r\n            DID info.\r\n          </li>\r\n          <li>\r\n            Set Destination - Select <strong>Extentions</strong> from the\r\n            options. Later select the extention which was created earlier.\r\n            <img\r\n              alt=\"Inbound route details\"\r\n              src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_10.png\"\r\n            />\r\n          </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Click <strong>Submit</strong>. Your Inbound route will be created.\r\n      </li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n\r\n    <p><strong>Asterisk SIP Settings</strong></p>\r\n\r\n    <ol class=\"numbered\">\r\n      <li>\r\n        From <strong>Setting</strong> menu, click\r\n        <strong>Asterisk SIP Settings</strong>.\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Next, enter the following details in the <strong>General</strong>\r\n        <strong>SIP Settings</strong> tab:\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>\r\n            <strong>External Address</strong> - Click on &lsquo;<strong\r\n              >Detect Network Settings</strong\r\n            >&rsquo; and copy the value for future reference\r\n            <img\r\n              alt=\"Asterisk SIP Settings\"\r\n              src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_7.png\"\r\n            />\r\n          </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Next, enter the following details in the <strong>Chan</strong>\r\n        <strong>SIP Settings</strong> tab in\r\n        <strong>Advance General Settings</strong> section :\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li><strong>Bind port</strong> - 5060</li>\r\n          <li>\r\n            <strong>TLS Bind Port</strong> - 5061\r\n            <img\r\n              alt=\"Port details\"\r\n              src=\"./Zentrunk API Documentation_files/image_8.png\"\r\n            />\r\n          </li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </li>\r\n      <li>\r\n        Click <strong>Apply Config</strong> on the top navigation bar. All your\r\n        configurations are complete. You can now configure X-Lite to use your\r\n        Trunk. <strong>Note:</strong> In case you get an error while configuring\r\n        your softphone, make sure you have clicked\r\n        <strong>Apply Config</strong> on FreePBX.\r\n      </li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>', NULL, 0, NULL, 0, 0, 'page', NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, 1, NULL, '2020-08-28 05:55:58', '2020-08-28 06:08:43'),
